The article states that there has been progress in reducing global inflation in the US economy. Prices have remained stable in the country over the past two months, which is good news for American families. Gas prices have dropped an average of $1.30 per gallon since the summer. Although there have been some price increases at grocery stores, they have slowed down compared to the previous month. Additionally, real wages have increased for the second consecutive month, providing some relief for hard-working families. The article acknowledges that it will take time and determination to further reduce inflation. The Inflation Reduction Act has been passed to address the high costs of healthcare, prescription drugs, and energy. The author also mentions that their economic plan is creating well-paying jobs and bringing manufacturing back to America as prices decrease.